{{Nihongo|'''Hiroki Ito'''|伊藤 洋輝|Itō Hiroki|born 12 May 1999}} is a Japanese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]], [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]] and [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]] for {{German football updater|BaMunich}} club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].

==Club career==
===Júbilo Iwata===
After growing through [[Júbilo Iwata]] youth ranks, Hiroki Ito was promoted to the first team in 2018.<ref name="gekisaka">{{cite web|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?216625-216625-fl|title=磐田、U-19日本代表MF伊藤洋輝とプロ契約「世界で活躍する選手に」 {{pipe}} ゲキサカ|website=web.gekisaka.jp|date=19 May 2017 |accessdate=22 August 2018}}</ref> He debuted as a pro in March 2018 in [[J. League Cup]], and would soon make his first appearance in [[J1 League]] in August 2018.<ref name="gekisaka2">{{cite web|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/jleague/detail/?252375-252375-fl|title=意地問われる中位対決...松本昌、大久保のW移籍後初ゴールで磐田に軍配 {{pipe}} ゲキサカ|website=web.gekisaka.jp|date=19 August 2018 |accessdate=22 August 2018}}</ref> In 2019, he was loaned out to [[Nagoya Grampus]], where he made nine appearances in all competitions.<ref name="auto1">{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/who-is-hiroki-ito-vfb-stuttgart-japan-defender-rookie-of-the-month-18168 |title=Hiroki Ito: Who is the VfB Stuttgart and Japan defender? |publisher=Bundesliga |date=21 December 2023 }}</ref>

===VfB Stuttgart===
In June 2021, Ito joined [[Bundesliga]] club [[VfB Stuttgart]] on loan, and was assigned to play for the [[VfB Stuttgart II|second team]] in the [[Regionalliga Südwest]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/neues/junge-wilde/2021/transfer-hiroki-ito-kopie/ |title=Hiroki Ito wechselt zum VfB |publisher=VfB Stuttgart |language=de |date=23 June 2021 }}</ref> However, he was instantly promoted to the first team by coach [[Pellegrino Matarazzo]], and started his first match in a 6–0 away win against [[Berliner FC Dynamo|BFC Dynamo]] in the [[2021–22 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]].<ref name="auto1"/> Afterwards that year, on 26 November, he scored his first Bundesliga goal in a 2–1 win over [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/profis/saison/bundesliga/2122/13-vfb-stuttgart----1--fsv-mainz-05-/ |title=Zwei Premierentore bringen den Sieg |publisher=VfB Stuttgart |language=de |date=26 November 2021 }}</ref> On 20 May 2022, VfB Stuttgart exercised a purchase option which tied Ito to the club with a contract until June 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2122/vfb-stuttgart-zieht-kaufoption-bei-hiroki-ito/|title=VfB take up purchase option on Hiroki Ito|work=vfb.de|publisher=[[VfB Stuttgart]]|date=20 May 2022|access-date=20 May 2022}}</ref>

In August 2023, he extended his contract with Stuttgart until June 2027.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2324/vertragsverlaengerung-hiroki-ito/|title=Hiroki Ito signs contract extension|work=vfb.de|publisher=[[VfB Stuttgart]]|date=23 August 2023|access-date=23 August 2023}}</ref> In the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|2023–24 season]], he played a crucial role in his club's runner-up finish and qualification to the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Ubina |first=Carlos |url=https://www.stuttgarter-zeitung.de/inhalt.abwehrspieler-des-vfb-stuttgart-das-macht-hiroki-ito-auch-fuer-den-fc-bayern-und-borussia-dortmund-interessant.db7d9002-0ec7-4ef0-ae61-4566afd5a196.html |title=Das macht Hiroki Ito auch für den FC Bayern und Borussia Dortmund interessant |publisher=Stuttgarter Zeitung |language=de |date=9 May 2024 }}</ref>

===Bayern Munich===
On 13 June 2024, Ito signed for fellow Bundesliga club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] until 2028,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/news/2024/06/neuzugang-vom-vfb-stuttgart-fc-bayern-verpflichtet-hiroki-ito |title=FC Bayern verpflichtet Hiroki Ito |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |language=de |date=13 June 2024 }}</ref> after they had triggered his release clause of an estimated €30 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sport.sky.de/fussball/artikel/hiroki-ito-wechselt-offiziell-vom-vfb-stuttgart-zum-fc-bayern/13152329/34943 |title=Offiziell! Bayern verpflichtet VfB-Star |work=Sky Sport |language=de |date=13 June 2024 }}</ref> However, he sustained a [[metatarsal]] fracture during the summer preseason which kept him sidelined for the first half of the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{cite web |last=Hoffmann |first=Torben |url=https://sport.sky.de/fussball/artikel/hiroki-ito-kuendigt-rueckkehr-ins-bayern-mannschaftstraining-ein/13297911/34369 |title=Hiroki Ito kündigt Rückkehr ins Bayern-Mannschaftstraining ein |publisher=Sky Sport |language=de |date=27 January 2025 }}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 12 February 2025, during a 2–1 away victory over [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League knockout phase]] play-offs.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tribuna.com/de/news/2025-02-12-hiroki-ito-gibt-sein-debut-bayern-munchen-besiegt-celtic-glasgow-im-hinspiel-mit-21/ |title=Hiroki Ito gibt sein Debüt: Bayern München besiegt Celtic Glasgow im Hinspiel mit 2:1 |publisher=Tribuna.com |language=de |date=12 February 2025 }}</ref> Later that month, on 23 February, he scored his first goal in a 4–0 victory over [[Eintracht Frankfurt]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Merritt |first=Jordan |url=https://www.si.com/onsi/soccer/bayern-munich/matchday/bayern-munich-4-0-eintracht-frankfurt-first-goal-for-hiroki-ito-as-bayern-dominate |title=Bayern Munich 4-0 Eintracht Frankfurt: First Goal For Hiroki Ito As Bayern Dominate |publisher=Sports Illustrated |date=23 February 2025 }}</ref> A month later, on 29 March, he suffered another metatarsal fracture during a 3–2 victory over [[FC St. Pauli|St. Pauli]], ruling him out for the remainder of the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2025/03/hiroki-ito-suffers-metatarsal-fracture |title=Hiroki Itō suffers metatarsal fracture |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |date=30 March 2025 }}</ref> Later that year, on 22 November, he made his comeback from a lengthy injury absence, recording an assist as a substitute in a 6–2 victory over [[SC Freiburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2025/11/freiburg-analysis |title=Allianz Arena in raptures: Olise & Karl shine in goalfest |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |date=22 November 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
Ito played for the youth teams of Japan, including the [[Japan national under-23 football team|U23 team]] during the [[2018 AFC U-23 Championship|2018 AFC Championship]],<ref>{{cite news|title=U-21 Japan National Team squad, schedule – AFC U-23 Championship China 2018|url=https://www.jfa.jp/eng/news/00015909/|accessdate=28 December 2017|date=26 December 2017}}</ref> the [[Japan national under-19 football team|U19 team]] in the [[2018 AFC U-19 Championship|2018 AFC Championship]],<ref>{{cite web|title=U-19 Japan National Team squad, schedule – AFC U-19 Championship Indonesia 2018 (10/18–11/4)|url=https://www.jfa.jp/eng/national_team/u19_2018/news/00018975/|publisher=JFA|date=2 October 2018}}</ref> and the [[Japan national under-20 football team|U20 team]] in the [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup|2019 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=FIFA U-20ワールドカップポーランド2019（5/23～6/15） U-20日本代表 メンバー・スケジュール |url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00021167/ |website=jfa.jp |publisher=JFA |access-date=7 May 2019 |language=ja |date=7 May 2019}}</ref>

Ito made his debut for the senior [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]] on 2 June 2022, during a 4–1 friendly win over [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/internationals/2022/zusammenfassung-laenderspielphase-juni-2022/|title=Ito debuts, Mavropanos goes the distance|website=vfb.de|date=15 June 2022|access-date=20 June 2022}}</ref> Later that year, on 1 November, he was selected in 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jfa.jp/eng/samuraiblue/news/00030869/ |title=Samurai Blue (Japan National Team) squad – FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022 |publisher=[[Japan Football Association]] |date=1 November 2022 |access-date=1 November 2022}}</ref>

He scored his first goal for Japan against [[Peru national football team|Peru]] on 20 June 2023 during the [[Kirin Cup Soccer#2023 Kirin Challenge Cup|Kirin Challenge Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jfa.jp/eng/samuraiblue/20230620/match_page.html |title=Japan 4–1 Peru |publisher=Japan Football Association |date=20 June 2023 }}</ref> On 1 January 2024, he was called up for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://jfa.jp/eng/news/00033539/ |title=SAMURAI BLUE (Japan National Team) squad – AFC Asian Cup Qatar 2023 |date=1 January 2024 |publisher=Japan Football Association |access-date=1 January 2024}}</ref>

